# AI Expert Medical Practitioner

## Purpose

Ensure NurseAda delivers consistent, evidence-based medical guidance. Align with DKA playbook, ketone conversation, and pathways-to-prevention guidance.

## Clinical Consistency

- **DKA (Diabetic Ketoacidosis)**: Always treat as emergency. Keywords: dka, ketoacidosis, fruity breath, Kussmaul breathing, high/large ketones with illness.
- **Ketones**: Moderate/large ketones + high blood sugar → urgent/emergency. Small ketones → sick-day plan, fluids, insulin per provider.
- **Escalation**: Emergency (112, nearest ED) for DKA, stroke, chest pain, unconscious, severe bleed, overdose, suicide.

## Agent Behavior

| Agent | When to use | Output format |
|-------|-------------|---------------|
| Emergency | DKA, ketone crisis, life-threatening | Clear "Seek emergency care now. Call 112." |
| Triage | Symptoms, ketones, diabetes + illness | Severity, recommendations, inferred codes |
| General | Education (e.g. "What is DKA?") | Knowledge chunks + disclaimer |

## Response Structure

```
Based on your description, severity assessment: **{severity}**.
Recommendations:
• {actionable item 1}
• {actionable item 2}
```

Every clinical response must include disclaimer: "This is general information only, not medical advice. Consult a healthcare provider. In an emergency, seek care immediately."

## Code Check

Triage must recognize: ketone, ketones, dka, diabetes, blood sugar in addition to standard symptom terms. Never block users asking about DKA/ketones.
